%^CYAN%^GOLDEN RULES%^RESET%^

%^MAGENTA%^These rules have been put in place to make the game fair and enjoyable for everyone. Knowing and abiding by these rules are conditions for playing Sundering Shadows.%^RESET%^

If you notice something that may be illegal, or if you encounter a dispute with another player or staff-member, contact the law team at %^ORANGE%^admin@sunderingshadows.com%^RESET%^ or via the %^ORANGE%^<lawmail>%^RESET%^ command.

%^ULINE%^%^MAGENTA%^Rule 1:%^RESET%^ Be kind and respectful towards your fellow players and our staff. This is a game, and we can settle/adjudicate all disagreements amicably. Though the game allows you to role-play an evil character, always be considerate out of character (OOC).
 
%^ULINE%^%^MAGENTA%^Rule 2:%^RESET%^ We are a role-playing MUD. When interacting with the game world, you are expected to stay in character (IC) whenever possible to increase immersion. 

%^ULINE%^%^MAGENTA%^Rule 3:%^RESET%^ Speak (write) English. Avoid using modern abbreviations.

%^ULINE%^%^MAGENTA%^Rule 4:%^RESET%^ Any scripts, triggers, etc. that automate combat are illegal.

%^ULINE%^%^MAGENTA%^Rule 5:%^RESET%^ Antagonistic actions may only occur between characters who have dropped their NOPK flag. See %^ORANGE%^<pk rules>%^RESET%^ and %^ORANGE%^<post pk rules>%^RESET%^. You are required to write a %^ORANGE%^<pkmail>%^RESET%^ in the following circumstances: 
    %^MAGENTA%^<>%^RESET%^ When you are involved in, or witness, a player vs player event, regardless of the outcome.
    %^MAGENTA%^<>%^RESET%^ When you commit, or are involved in, an action that makes you wanted in a city, even if that action was unintentional.
    %^MAGENTA%^<>%^RESET%^ This applies even if you have a NOPK-flag or choose to invoke the %^ORANGE%^<fade away>%^RESET%^ rule.

%^ULINE%^%^MAGENTA%^Rule 6:%^RESET%^ Sexual encounters require the OOC consent of all players involved. Consent may be withdrawn at any time without question. All participating characters must be adult members of their race.

%^ULINE%^%^MAGENTA%^Rule 7:%^RESET%^ Respect all Fade to Black requests immediately. See %^ORANGE%^<help fade to black>%^RESET%^ and %^ORANGE%^<help fade away>%^RESET%^.

%^ULINE%^%^MAGENTA%^Rule 8:%^RESET%^ You are allowed multiple characters, known as alts, under the following conditions:
    %^MAGENTA%^<>%^RESET%^ A player can have only one alt logged on at any given time. 
    %^MAGENTA%^<>%^RESET%^ Nothing can be transferred between your alts. 
    %^MAGENTA%^<>%^RESET%^ Your alts cannot know each other. If one alt permanently retires (mechanically or otherwise), you may request creating a new alt that is related to your old one. 
    %^MAGENTA%^<>%^RESET%^ A player should not have two (or more) alts directly involved on two (or more) sides of a conflict. 
    %^MAGENTA%^<>%^RESET%^ If one of your alts is involved in a PK, you should prioritize playing that alt for the next 7 days, or until the conflict has been resolved.

%^ULINE%^%^MAGENTA%^Rule 9:%^RESET%^ Offline collaboration is allowed, but attempts to demand or sleuth another's personal information will not be tolerated. OOC threats or abuse in any form, in game or out of game, is illegal.

%^ULINE%^%^MAGENTA%^Rule 10:%^RESET%^ Using this game as a medium to conduct illegal activities is strictly forbidden and will always result in rid and banishment. All character interactions are logged and may be observed by our staff.

In addition to these rules, you are expected to know and abide by the rules listed in %^ORANGE%^<help pk rules>%^RESET%^, %^ORANGE%^<help post pk rules>%^RESET%^ and %^ORANGE%^<help line use>%^RESET%^. Failure to comply with the rules will result in punishment and repeat offenders may be banned and/or rid. See also %^ORANGE%^<help shorthand>%^RESET%^ for a list of common abbreviations and their meaning. If these rules are unclear, contact our staff for clarification. 

%^CYAN%^SEE ALSO: %^RESET%^shorthand, pk rules, post pk rules, alts, line use, fade to black, fade away, languages, roleplaying, game, lawmail, avatarmail, pkmail, races, set
